data.description:
In this kata, you will be given an exception. Your job will be to throw that exception and cause it to bubble up through the stack, without using a throws declaration. The tester is designed so that it will generate a compiler error if you have a throws declaration. The idea is that a user could change the following:

```java
try {
  // generate some errors
} catch (Exception e) {
  e.printStackTrace();
}
```

to the following:

```java
try {
  // generate some errors
} catch (Exception e) {
  HackTheException.sneakyThrow(e);
}
```

so that the exception bubbles up and crashes the thread if necessary, without wrapping it in a `RuntimeException`, so that if it gets printed it doesn't print as a `RuntimeException`.
